title: For Sale:  Winchester 1895
postcontent: Winchester 1895 Chambered in 30-40 Krag. Its a very unique gun, and has been my favorite piece that ive owned. It is a lever action with a magazine, the first of its kind I do believe. After research ive deteremind that the gun itself is an american variant that was made somewhere around 1904-1905. There is a chance it could even be a pinkerton gun, but there are not many records from back then, so its really a guessing game. It shoots amazing and feeds like it should. I have never encountered a problem with it, pretty impressive for a 100+ year old gun. This was Teddy Roosevelts favorite model gun, which makes its DOB even cooler (made the same time he was in office). These guns go anywhere from $6k to $500. Caliber and condition considered, I am asking $1700 obo. Please text me, Tyler, if you have any questions or would like more pictures.

title: For Sale:  NOS Rare Gyrojet Mk.II 12mm Rocket
postcontent: Original and unfired MBAssociates Gyrojet Rocket Pistol in factory box with owner's manual and ephemera...this pistol was manufactured in California around 1968 and is unfired(NOS) condition. A scarce find on the collector's market, the Gyrojet is a true oddity that, while well-hyped and innovative, was made for too brief a period to be properly refined. Made of Zamak, the pistol was a light, 7-round, smoothbore launchpad that ignited the solid rocket fuel of a .49(12mm), brass, bullet-shaped cartridge(today rarer than the gun itself). Although considered for development by the military-the Gyrojet functioned quite well under water-the gun was never used in any official capacity. Despite claims of its service with Special Forces in Vietnam, no known, documented incidents of the Gyrojet being used in combat exist, but the gun is familiar to James Bond fans, having played a prominent role in 1967's "You Only Live Twice". Complete with its original box and manual, the pistol includes articles and a catalog listing with the original retail
